name: media_png_invalid_text_transfer_signature
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG whose only mutation is in the eight-byte signature:
  the CR LF sequence has become LF LF, a classic symptom of text-mode transfer
  damage. The rest of the file is a valid 1x1 RGBA PNG. This should fail at
  signature validation, before chunk parsing starts.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  PNG Suite documents corrupted files caused by non-binary transfers, and the
  PNG specification defines the exact signature bytes:
  https://www.libpng.org/pub/png/pngsuite.html
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#5PNG-file-signature
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "known-problematic"
  - "png-suite-inspired"
  - "signature"
  - "text-transfer"
---
89 50 4e 47 0a 0a 1a 0a
00 00 00 0d 49 48 44 52 00 00 00 01 00 00 00 01 08 06 00 00 00 1f 15 c4 89
00 00 00 0b 49 44 41 54 78 da 63 60 00 02 00 00 05 00 01 e9 fa dc d8
00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82
